   Carl Blackman, who contributed to
Guyanese journalism for more than 40 years, died Thursday of a
heart ailment. He was 67.
   Blackman wrote for the old Daily Chronicle, the Guyana Graphic,
the state-owned Guyana Chronicle, the Trinidad Evening News, the
Trinidad Guardian and the Guyana National Newspapers Limited. He
also was an Associated Press stringer in Guyana.
   Seven years ago Blackman retired as first general manager and
editor-in-chief of the Guyana National Newspapers Limited. He
continued to write his popular columns regularly for the Sunday
Chronicle until shortly before his death.
