<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--JeopardyMistake     02-23 0184</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Jeopardy Mistake,0191</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Game Show Apologizes To Kansas City, Kan.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The producer of ``Jeopardy'' has
apologized to Mayor Joseph E. Steineger Jr. because a question on
the television game show referred to the city as a suburb of Kansas
City, Mo.
   But producer George Vosburgh stopped short of conceding an error.
   ``We are taking Kansas City, Kansas, out of our definition of a
suburb,'' said Vosburgh, who sent a written apology to the mayor
last week.
   ``We are not necessarily incorrect. ... We just will not refer
to it that way in the future.''
   The show intends to clear up the matter and other recent
misunderstandings with an ``Oops'' category in a future show.
   After hearing about the reference to his city on a December
show, Steineger wrote an indignant letter to the producer, saying
Kansas City, Kan., was a city in its own right.
   Steineger said he was satisfied, though still somewhat miffed.
   ``I guess when the mayor said they were wrong, they were
wrong,'' he said. ``We certainly like to be recognized as our own
city.''
</TEXT>
