<HEAD>Secretary Of State Says Weather Shouldn't Affect Voter Turnout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PIERRE, S.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Secretary of State Joyce Hazeltine says she
doubts that today's weather will affect voter turnout, and she
still expects about one-half the state's registered Republicans and
one-third of the Democrats to vote in the presidential primary.
   The weather forecast calls for strong winds but no snow, she
said.
   The secretary of state said the fact that Vice President George
Bush withdrew from active competition in the South Dakota primary
will not affect Republican voter turnout.
   ``How I see that. Those who are for him are going to vote for
him anyway. Those who are angry with him for that are going to come
out and vote for (Bob) Dole.''
</TEXT>
