<HEAD>Texas Kemp Camp Issues Invitation To Disgruntled Dole, Robertson
Supporters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chairman of Rep. Jack Kemp's Texas campaign is
asking supporters of Sen. Bob Dole and Pat Robertson to abandon
their candidates and join the Kemp campaign because of the refusal
of Dole and Robertson to appear in a debate last week in Dallas.
   Bob Holland, the Kemp official, call the action by Robertson and
Dole a snub of Texas.
   ``By their failure to face George Bush in one of his home states
Friday night, Bob Dole made clear that he has written off Texas and
Pat Robertson committed another serious blunder casting further
doubts on his electability,'' Holland said.
   The withdrawals left only Kemp and Bush to debate.
