<HEAD>Soldier Killed At Hospital When Hand Grenade Slips From Belt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hand grenade slipped from the belt of a
Lebanese army officer and exploded today at a hospital in east
Beirut. Police said the officer was killed and four visitors were
injured.
   The grenade exploded in the morning in the visitors' lounge of
the Hayek Hospital in the Christian district of Sin el-Fil, a
police spokesman said.
   First Lt. Issam Rahmeh, who was visiting a patient, died
instantly and four other visitors were injured, said the spokesman,
who cannot be named in line with standing regulations.
   He said it had not been determined how the grenade slipped from
Rahmeh's belt. The army was investigating the incident.
