<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF-Spain-Fire     02-23 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Spain-Fire,0119</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fire Causes Slight Damage To Interior Ministry Offices</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire slightly damaged the office of
Interior Minister Jose Barrionuevo today, the ministry said. No
injuries were reported.
   A ministry spokesman said the fire apparently was caused by an
electrical short circuit in the second-floor office of the
minister's personal secretary and spread to three adjacent offices.
   Firefighters put out the fire in 15 minutes, the spokesman said.
   The Interior Ministry building is located near the central
Colombus Square on the city's main north-south thoroughfare.
   Barrionuevo was not in his office at the time the fire began,
although members of his press office, security guards and cleaning
help were.
</TEXT>
