<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Swaggart-Text     02-23 0293</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Swaggart-Text,0302</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Statement By Church Council Outlines Rehabilitation Plan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of a statement Monday
night by Cecil Janway, district superintendent of the Assemblies of
God, about the discipline recommended for evangelist Jimmy Swaggart:
   We accept his confession of specific incidents of a moral
failure. Based on this detailed confession and the evidence we
observed of true humility and repentance, we have offered him
rehabilitation in accordance with the bylaws of the General Council
and Louisiana District of the Assemblies of God.
   Brother Swaggart has submitted to the terms of rehabilitation as
follows:
   1. Brother Swaggart will begin a two-year rehabilitation period
effective immediately.
   2. Brother Swaggart will be required to refrain from preaching
for a minimum of three months, except in fulfillment of present
commitments involving foreign governments during that period.
   3. During the time of rehabilitation, Brother Swaggart will be
relieved of his duties as co-pastor of Family Worship Center,
retaining the right to preach in the Family Worship Center after
the period described in paragraph 2.
   4. Brother Swaggart will receive counsel and supervision in
weekly conferences with three members of the Louisiana District
Presbytery during the period of rehabilitation.
   5. Brother Swaggart will submit quarterly written reports to the
district superintendent and monthly written reports to his
sectional presbyter.
   Again, no doubt much speculation and rumor will find its way
into the secular media. But, for the church, the body of Christ,
such speculation and rumor has no place.
   We urge Brother Swaggart and his associates to resist the
request of those outside the church to respond to questions.
Brother Swaggart has been in complete cooperation with the
Assemblies of God and has pledged to work within the structure of
the church.
</TEXT>
