<HEAD>51 People Infected With Cholera, One Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cholera has infected 51 people in
northeastern Thailand and killed a 7-year-old girl, a health
official said today.
   Dr. Chin Yuwachit, public health chief of Udon Thai province,
said the disease has been brought under control since cases were
first reported in several districts on Feb. 8. Eleven victims
remain hospitalized, he said.
   Cholera is prevalent in areas in Asia where public sanitation is
poor. The acute infectious disease is caused by a bacteria found in
fecal-contaminated food and water. Its main symptom is severe
diarrhea.
</TEXT>
