<1ST_LINE>r a PM-ParentsSlain     02-23 0424</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Parents Slain,0436</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen-Ager Held Following Discovery of Parents' Bodies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 16-year-old boy has been arrested in
the deaths of his parents, whose bodies were found buried in a
shallow grave in the family's back yard, authorities said.
   A neighbor told police that the boy's father had recently shown
him a drawing by his son depicting a man with an ax in his head.
The boy reportedly told his father, ``That's what I feel like doing
to you.''
   The bodies of Peter and Karen Overhand were discovered about
midnight Sunday by police who went to the residence to check out
confidential information they had received.
   Mitchell Overhand, 16, the couple's only child, was being held
at the Juvenile Detention Center, the Bernalillo County Sheriff's
Department said. A second 16-year-old youth, whose name was
withheld, also was taken into custody. No charges have been brought
against the two.
   The Overhands, who were believed to be in their mid-30s to 40s,
were killed between 3 a.m. and 4 a.m. Thursday, probably while they
slept, said Sheriff's Capt. Dan Houston.
   An autopsy indicated Peter Overhand was shot with a .38-caliber
handgun, Houston said. An autopsy had not been completed on Mrs.
Overhand Monday night, but Houston said she also appeared to have
been shot.
   Four handguns were seized as evidence, but authorities would not
say where they were found or to whom they belonged.
   James Bradley, a neighbor, said Mitchell Overhand told friends
his parents were in California for the weekend attending his
grandfather's funeral.
   Sheriff's department spokeswoman Ronni Crago said police
received information that ``something of a suspicious nature'' had
happened at the Overhand home in a subdivision on Albuquerque's
West Mesa.
   Police obtained a search warrant and found the bodies, she said.
   C.D. Youngblood, who lives next door to the Overhands, said
Peter Overhand spoke to him often about problems he was having with
Mitchell.
   Overhand, Youngblood said, recently told him of finding a
drawing in the garbage depicting a man with an ax in his head. When
Peter Overhand confronted his son with the drawing, the younger
Overhand said, ``That's what I feel like doing to you,'' Youngblood
recalled.
   Mitchell Overhand, Bradley said, spent the weekend with friends
and had attended a party Friday night at an Albuquerque hotel. He
said the boy also had invited a number of friends to his home over
the weekend.
   Youngblood also said Peter Overhand told him his son hated him
so much, ``he wouldn't be surprised if he tried to kill him.''
</TEXT>
