<HEAD>American Speed Skater Takes Gold Medal With Record Time</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS lead to restore dropped word `winner'</NOTE>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto OLY43</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CALGARY, Alberta (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Speed skater Bonnie Blair set a world
record while becoming America's second gold medal winner at the
Winter Olympics.
   Blair's time of 39.10 seconds in Monday night's 500-meter race
nipped the record set minutes earlier by her East German archrival
Christa Rothenburger.
   ``I think I just got it on guts,'' Blair said.
   On Saturday, Brian Boitano of California won a gold medal in
figure skating. U.S. athletes also have won one silver and one
bronze medal.
   Rothenburger lowered her own world record by 0.27 second,
skating in the second pair in the women's 500 meters and finishing
in 39.12. Two pairs later, Blair, of Champaign, Ill., trimmed an
additional 0.02 second off the mark, winning the gold in 39.10.
Karin Kania of East Germany won the bronze.
   The Soviet Union leads with seven golds, and East Germany has
six.
