<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BoxerHero     02-23 0285</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Boxer Hero,0295</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Elderly Woman Rescued From Snow By Son's Boxer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLETON, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dog named Tootsie awakened her master
with a whine and led him outside to a snowdrift, where he found his
90-year-old mother curled up in her nightgown.
   Ethelyn Preston, who has Alzheimer's disease, was listed in
stable condition today at Swedish Medical Center in suburban
Englewood, where she is being treated for a broken right arm and
cuts.
   ``If Tootsie hadn't notified me, she would have died,'' said Roy
Preston, Mrs. Preston's 58-year-old son, who lives with her.
   Preston said his 3{-year-old boxer woke him up Friday morning,
``whining, like she wanted to tell me something,'' he said. ``Then
she ran right out to the back yard.''
   He followed the dog and found his mother lying on her right
side, slightly curled up in a snowdrift near the back door. She was
wearing a nightgown and was barefoot.
   ``When I saw her there, I was frantic,'' her son said. ``I
couldn't lift her. Her body was stiff. She was all dead weight from
lying out in the cold.''
   She had been outside about 15 minutes, he said.
   Preston got help from a neighbor and an ambulance.
   When the ambulance arrived, Tootsie pitched in again.
   ``She was running back and forth from where she (Ethelyn
Preston) was and the ambulance,'' her son said. ``It seemed like
she (Tootsie) wanted to tell them where my mother was.''
   Preston said his mother probably was trying to get to the
bathroom, next to her bedroom, when she lost her way and ended up
in the yard.
   He said he will hire round-the-clock supervision for her when
she gets home from the hospital.
</TEXT>
