<2ND_LINE>PM-Missing Passenger,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Coast Guard Searching For Woman Missing from Cruise Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 32-year-old woman was reported missing today from
a Bahamas-bound cruise ship, and the Coast Guard sent a jet and a
cutter to search for the woman.
   The husband of Cheryl Wainscott of Woodstock, Ga., told the
captain of the Carnivale that he last saw his wife at 12:30 a.m.
today when she went for a walk, said Coast Guard Petty Officer Joe
Dye.
   The husband said his wife had been depressed, Dye said.
   The cruise ship radioed the Coast Guard at about 9 a.m. today. A
falcon jet and the 95-foot cutter Cape Current were immediately
dispatched to search an area 70 miles northeast of Miami, near
Great Isaac Light, Dye said.
   The 640-foot, Miami-based Carnivale is owned by Carnival Cruise
Lines. It routinely makes three- to four-day trips to the Bahamas.
It set sail for Nassau at 4 p.m. Monday on one of those voyages,
said company spokesman Tim Gallagher.
</TEXT>
