<2ND_LINE>PM-Serial Assaults,0251</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Arrested, Linked To ``Bolder-Than-Most'' Rapist</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 26-year-old pipe fitter was arrested in
connection with a series of 19 sexual attacks in the San Diego area
blamed on a ``bolder-than-most'' rapist, police said.
   Alvin Ray Quarles was arrested Monday at a motel staked out by
police, said Officer Brian Monahan of the suburban National City
Police Department.
   Quarles was questioned by investigators at San Diego police
headquarters for several hours and booked into the county jail,
said San Diego police spokeswoman Linda Zweig.
   The series of rapes and burglaries began 14 months ago. The
attacker was dubbed ``bolder-than-most'' because of the audacity of
his demands and because he frequently attacked women when they were
with a boyfriend or husband.
   Quarles was charged in the investigation of two rapes and six
robberies and burglaries, Zweig said. The investigation is
continuing and more charges may be filed, she said.
   Quarles was arrested about 5 a.m. Monday after a police
detective spotted him peeking in windows and checking doors of the
motel, police said, adding that a 13-inch kitchen knife was found
hidden under his shirt.
   The arrest came an hour after a man forced his way into a room
at a motel in east San Diego where two elderly women were sleeping
and robbed the women but did not assault them.
   At least 16 of the sexual assaults occurred in San Diego, half
of them at small motels.
</TEXT>
