<HEAD>Police Arrest 75 Suspected Drug Dealers in Verona</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VERONA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 75 people suspected of
illegal drug trafficking in this northern city, authorities said
Tuesday.
   Police Chief Umberto Lucchese said the sweep was made at dawn
Sunday. He said warrants had also been issued to 27 people already
in jail, while police were unable to track down seven others to
serve the warrants.
   Police said those arrested were suspected of involvement in
small or medium-size drug operations.
   They said Sunday's operation had no connection with the seizure
last week of 187 pounds of nearly pure heroin found in two garages
in a village just outside Verona. Police arrested three men in that
case.
