<HEAD>Stock Prices Pull Back</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was drifting at modestly lower
levels this afternoon as its recent rally ran into some resistance.
   Trading was moderate.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which jumped 25.70
points on Monday to its highest level since Jan. 7, was off 3.82 at
2,036.47 with two hours to go in the session.
   Declining issues outpaced gainers by a margin of nearly 4 to 3
in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with
677 up, 816 down and 441 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 147.77 million shares as of 2
p.m. on Wall Street with 109.87 million shares at the same point on
Monday.
   Traders said the market seemed to pause after a sharp runup over
the past two weeks.
   They said traders were also looking for clues in Federal Reserve
Chairman Alan Greenspan's testimony to a congressional panel about
the central bank's view of the economy.
   The stock market has benefited recently from indications that
the economy may be stronger than had been expected, leading some
analysts to take an optimistic view of the outlook for corporate
profits.
   But there is plenty of uncertainty about the economy's prospects.
   In a new report today, the government said orders to U.S.
factories for durable goods plunged 2.8 percent in January, the
biggest decline in a year.
   Many analysts had expected a decline in January, however,
because orders had risen by an unusually large 4.1 percent in
December.
   Among the most active issues on the NYSE were several utility
stocks that will soon be paying dividends. Philadelphia Electric
was the most active, slipping [ to 19}.
   Among the blue chips, Eastman Kodak was down \ at 40{, American
Telephone & Telegraph was down [ at 29} and International Business
Machines was up \ at 115{.
   Moore McCormick climbed 10| to 34{ after Southdown disclosed it
was offering $31 a share for the company.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
off 0.54 at 148.42. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index fell 0.93 to 282.08.
