<HEAD>American, Delta Raise Fares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The cheapest round-trip fares on American Airlines
and Delta Air Lines, often used by vacationers, will increase $10
and similar fares offered by United Airlines also will go up,
company officials said.
   The increases are in so-called MaxSaver fares used on or after
March 2. If tickets are purchased before that date, but travel is
ater, additional cost will be included in the faon that day or lre
price, the airlines said Monday.
   MaxSaver tickets, only available on round-trip travel, are not
refundable and must be purchased within 24 hours of making
reservations.
   The price hike follows a fare increase announced by major
airlines last week. American and Delta, Dallas-Fort Worth airport's
dominant carriers, as well as Braniff Inc. and other major airlines
said they would raise unrestricted coach fares by $5 each way on
most routes.
